Who is a SOC Analyst (L1)?
The first line of defence in an organisation's cyber monitoring team. Responsible for monitoring, triaging, and escalating security alerts.
It's an entry-level Blue Team role that runs on 24x7 shift coverage.

Core Responsibilities:
Monitoring security alerts via SIEM tools
Alert triage — analysing logs for IP, URL, and User-Agent data to spot anomalies
Knowing when and how to escalate (not every alert needs escalation)
Logging incident tickets via JIRA/ServiceNow
Reporting & documentation — daily shift logs, incident summaries, status reports

Tools an L1 Uses:
SIEM (log monitoring): Splunk, Wazuh, ELK
Ticketing: ServiceNow, JIRA
Threat Intel: VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB
Communication: Slack, Email, MS Teams

SOC Team Hierarchy: 
Security Analysts → Incident Responders → Threat Hunters → SOC Manager → Security Engineers 
Each branch has its own specialisation (e.g., Analysts do monitoring/triage/collaboration, threat Hunters do advanced detection/vulnerability assessment,
the Manager does strategic planning/team management).
